  "response_text": "A dark-haired adult man in a suit and tie faces forward against a dark blue studio background. He has a serious, intent expression, with his brows slightly drawn together, and speaks directly toward the viewer. He raises one hand into view holding several small medicine bottles close to his face. Three white plastic bottles are grouped together: one clearly labeled “Datril,” one smaller white bottle with a red cap and a pale label, and a larger red-and-white bottle labeled “Extra-Strength Tylenol.” He then brings in a separate brown bottle with a white cap and a yellow label, holding it on the other side so it stands apart from the three white bottles. The yellow label reads “ANACIN” in large black letters, with “FAST PAIN RELIEF” below it.\n\nThe Anacin bottle is then shown larger and more prominently. A hand steadies the brown bottle so the label can be read: “ANACIN,” “FAST PAIN RELIEF,” and smaller lines including “HEADACHE,” “COLDS/BODY ACHE,” and “NEURALGIA.” The hand withdraws, leaving the bottle standing alone on a smooth surface against the same dark blue background. White block lettering appears beside it: “ANACIN REDUCES INFLAMMATION THAT COMES WITH PAIN.”\n\nThe other pain reliever bottles slide back into view to the right of the Anacin bottle. A hand passes over the tops of the three competing bottles, touching or indicating them as a group, while the Anacin bottle remains separate on the left. The arrangement visually contrasts the single brown Anacin bottle with the cluster of white and red bottles beside it.\n\nThe scene changes to a stylized black silhouette of a standing human body, seen from the front against a glowing blue background. The figure’s arms hang slightly away from the sides, fists down. Large white words appear over and around the body to identify different pain-related areas. “TOOTH EXTRACTION” fills the screen in oversized letters, then the figure is shown again with small red-orange glowing spots marking areas of discomfort, including near the neck and lower body. “MUSCLE STRAINS” appears near the lower torso. Another oversized word passes across the body, followed by “BACKACHE” across the middle of the torso. More red-orange starburst marks appear on the body as the words “TENDONITIS” and then “NEURITIS” are shown, with the silhouette still centered against the blue background.\n\nThe product lineup returns on the tabletop. From left to right are the brown Anacin bottle, the white Datril bottle, the smaller white bottle with a red cap, and the larger red-and-white Extra-Strength Tylenol bottle. Along the bottom, small white text reads, “USE ONLY AS DIRECTED.” A hand again moves over the three non-Anacin bottles, indicating them together. The hand then moves away, leaving the Anacin bottle visually separated from the others.\n\nFinally, the suited man reappears against the dark blue background. He lifts the brown Anacin bottle beside his face and holds it toward the viewer. Large white text appears to his left reading “ADULT STRENGTH.” He looks forward with a firm, composed expression while presenting the bottle, its yellow “ANACIN” label facing outward.",
